50|$|Net {{national}} income (NNI) is an economics term used in {{national income}} accounting. It {{can be defined}} as the <b>net</b> <b>national</b> <b>product</b> (NNP) minus indirect taxes. Net national income encompasses the income of households, businesses, and the government. Net national income is the difference between what is earned by nationals living outside the country and non-nationals living in the country.|$|E
